Instructions for building a docker image for OGBG : 

1) cd into algorithmic-efficiency/algorithmic_efficiency/docker/
2) docker build -t mlcommons:ogbg ./

To Test the built image you can run :
3) docker run -it mlcommons:ogbg 

If you're building docker image on a GCP VM (recommended) then do 

```
gcloud auth configure-docker us-central1-docker.pkg.dev
```

To Push built image to artifact regiistory on GCP do this : 

```
    docker tag mlcmmons:ogbg  us-central1-docker.pkg.dev/training-algorithms-external/mlcommons-docker-repo/mlcommons:ogbg
    docker push us-central1-docker.pkg.dev/training-algorithms-external/mlcommons-docker-repo/mlcommons:ogbg
```

This is required when you deploy the built image on a GCP VM

If you're using cloud build to build docker image you can run : 
```
gcloud builds submit     --region=us-west2 --config     cloudbuild.yaml
```

Recommendation : Use a GCP VM to build mlcommons docker image. Do not use cloudshell to build mlcommons docker images as the cloudshell provisioned machine runs out of storage